olive oil
1 carrot
1 courgette
1 potato
1 packet beef mince
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 egg
1 packet tomato paste
1 packet garlic paste
1 sachet beef-style stock powder
2 cup water
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet parsley

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut carrot, courgette and potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, combine beef mince, fine breadcrumbs, garlic & herb seasoning and the egg in a medium bowl.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of beef mixture into small meatballs (5-6 per person). Transfer to a plate.

• In a large saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook meatballs, turning, until browned 6-8 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).

• Add tomato paste and garlic paste to the saucepan and cook, stirring until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add beef-style stock powder and the water. Bring to the boil, then reduce heat to medium and simmer until slightly reduced, 3-4 minutes.

• Add roasted veggies and baby leaves, stirring until wilted, 1-2 minutes.

• Divide beef meatball and veggie soup between bowls.
• Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!